The group was signed by the Elektra record company, where it would remain for the eight years of its existence.
Elektra released Bread's first album, Bread, in 1969, which peaked at No. 127 on the Billboard 200.

In late 1978, they toured billing themselves as "David Gates & Bread", which brought a lawsuit from Griffin, who was still co-owner of the Bread trademark, and an injunction against the use of the name Bread.
